  "title": "sfb_meg_phantom (B04/C01)",
  "description": "This dataset contains magnetoencephalography (MEG) recordings from a Neuromag phantom used to characterize device-specific artifacts generated by deep brain stimulation (DBS) systems. The study investigates how DBS-related electromagnetic interference affects MEG signal quality and measurement reliability, providing essential reference data for researchers working with concurrent DBS-MEG recordings in clinical and research settings.",
  "methods_description": "MEG recordings were acquired using a Neuromag phantom system. Movement onset was recorded with an accelerometer and captured in MISC006-MISC008 channels.",
